Author: Frederic Bertrand [cre, aut] (<https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0837-8281>)
Maintainer: Frederic Bertrand <frederic.bertrand@lecnam.net>
Description: Adds variable-selection functions for Beta regression models
    (mean submodel) so they can be used within the 'SelectBoost' algorithm.
    Includes stepwise 'AIC'/'BIC'/'AICc' on betareg() fits, 'GAMLSS'-based LASSO/Elastic-Net,
    a pure 'glmnet' 'IRLS'-based selector with an optional standardization speedup,
    and C++ helpers for 'IRLS' working steps and precision updates. Also provides
    a fastboost_interval() variant for interval responses, comparison helpers,
    and a flexible simulator simulation_DATA.beta() for interval-valued data.
